(64107, 183317, 0, 1, 'The Silence Has Broken', 'From the Floating On The Breeze CD from 2003.\nRecorded at home in Sweden by Antony Harding.', '2013-05-30 00:00:00', 2000, 19, 1, 7, 'THE SILENCE HAS BROKEN\n\nWalk with me as far as we can see\nWe''re too busy dreaming of the movies\nAnd talk to me with words that I can hear\nJust turn your little voice up a bit louder\n\nNow that the silence has broken fill it where we stand \nAnd count all the words we''ve spoken on the fingers of your hand\nOn the fingers of your hand\n\nWalk with me through the parks to the sea \nWe''re too busy living in a daydream\nAnd talk to me with words I''ll never learn \nAnd turn your little voice up a little bit louder\n\nNow that the silence has broken fill it where we stand\nAnd count all the words we''ve spoken on the fingers of your hand\nOn the fingers of your hand\n\nOh it''s easy to be carefree when the summer lasts so long\nOh it''s easy to be blasé when the days can do no wrong\nDon''t worry if there are never enough hours in one day\nFor tomorrow starts anew and today the dream came true\n\nNow that the silence has broken fill it where we stand \nAnd count all the words we''ve spoken on the fingers of your hand\nOn the fingers of your hand\nOn the fingers of your hand\nOn the fingers of your hand  ', '', 253, '', 'Antony Harding', 'Antony Harding', 'Antony Harding', 'Homesleep Music (ITALY) ', '', 0, 1, 0, '2013-05-30 18:03:32', '2015-03-12 14:00:52', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
